title: EKVX-Scrb-1
growth_protocol_ch1: EKVX-cells were plated in T-25 flask at 2x106 density and cultivated in Dulbecco's minimal essential medium (DMEM) supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum, 100 U/mL penicillin and 100 mg/mL streptomycin at 37°C in 5% CO2 overnight. Then, cells were washed 3 times with PBS and cultured in DMEM media supplemented with 10% exosome-depleted FBS (System Biosciences, Inc. (SBI), Palo Alto, CA) for 48 hours
extract_protocol_ch1: Exosomes were isolated from cell culture media using using ExoQuick-TCTM (SBI), and microRNA was purified using QIAGEN miRNeasy micro kit (QIAGEN, Valencia, CA) per the manufacture’s protocols
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Libraries were prepared according to standard Ilumina's instructions
data_processing: miRNA sequencing short reads were aligned to human reference genome (GRCh38) using Bowtie2 (v2.2.3) ;
data_processing.1: Aligned sequences were mapped to mature miRNAs with annotation from miRBase (v.21);
data_processing.2: The relative expression abundances of miRNAs were calculated as Count-Per-Million (CPM).
